Are you ready to deepen your understanding of the quantum field and learn how to create brain & heart coherence? If so, Dr Joe created The Formula Online Course just for you. This Labor Day weekend, discover exclusive bundles to get you back to school in the right mindset. This introductory level course provides step-by-step guidance that is based on 30 years of research on the science of personal change and transformation. It is a scientifically proven, practical formula that countless people are effectively applying to their own lives to create change from within.

If you are a student of Dr Joe’s work or wish to become one, The Formula Online Course should be at the top of your syllabus. Starting today, we are featuring The Formula Online Course in two exclusive bundles. See below for details.

▪️Back to School Online Bundle: The Formula Online Course & “Introduction to Breaking the Habit of Being Yourself” (Audio Lecture)

▪️AP Class Online Bundle: The Formula Online Course, “Introduction to Breaking the Habit of Being Yourself” (Audio Lecture), “Breaking the Habit of Being Yourself” (Audio Book), and the two accompanying meditations for the book, “Water Rising” and “Body Parts – Space.”

The Formula Online Course Back to School Bundles are available until Tuesday September 7 at 3 p.m. PT.

Learning is more fun together—tag a few friends with whom you’d want to start The Formula Online Course. Learn more by clicking the link in our bio.

Already completed The Formula Online Course? Share your experience in the comments below and using the #DrJoeTheFormula

These subscription-based conversations are for anybody who is interested in transforming their life.

Click the link in bio to learn more & register to join Dr Joe and the rest of the community for this month’s conversation, on Thursday August 26th 12:00pm (PST) // 3:00PM (EST) on Zoom. Register early so as to receive your Zoom link in time.

While these conversations are live, the two most recent episodes can also be accessed later in the subscriber’s online library.

When you join Dr Joe Live, you’ll also be the first to know about our upcoming planned Live Events before they are posted on our website as we announce at the end of each class. 

Dr Joe Live is available in English, Spanish, German & French.

After a mystical experience during one of the meditations at a recent Week Long Advanced Retreat, Nicole had the knowingness that she would feel better if she stopped taking thyroid medication for Hashimoto's disease. She went off of the medication -- but continued daily meditation -- and the lab results show her thyroid function in the normal range.

Recorded at the Marco Island Advanced Follow-Up Retreat in April 2021

UPDATE from Nicole - June 5, 2021:
"I need to add to my testimony... At this same time I was having histamine reactions to foods, rashes on my body, and finding less and less foods I could eat without my body reacting like an allergic reaction. Totally gone. I came into the Week Long with a rash on my stomach and it was gone! Boom gone! I did not react to one food since this retreat. I even had dairy and bread during the Week Long. Since this experience, my husband is on this train and two on my teenagers. I’m in love with life and with my body! Thank you anyone this helps!!!"

Bonnie was invited on stage at the Orlando Advanced Week Long Retreat to share her story of healing from Guillain-Barre Syndrome, a rare autoimmune condition that can lead to complete paralysis. Her diagnosis was later changed to Chronic Inflammatory Demyelinating Polyneuropathy, with a similar dire prognosis. Bonnie was a Give to Give Foundation scholarship recipient. For more information about Give to Give:
https://givetogivefoundation.org

From Bonnie (posted on Facebook 5/25/21):
I can honestly say that one of the greatest highlights of my life was getting up on this stage in front of 1,350 people and sharing my story about how I healed myself from a chronic autoimmune disease, CIDP.
I was originally diagnosed w/ GBS and then it was changed to Chronic Inflammatory Demyelinating Polyneuropathy. I lost the feeling of and ability to move or use my feet and legs.
I was told that I could be dependent on a walker or wheelchair for the rest of my life and that I would need either the treatments such as plasma exchange or IV treatments or steroids or other medications (all w/ harmful side effects) for the rest of my life.
I was introduced to the work of Dr Joe Dispenza and I immersed myself into his work and this is what I attribute my healing to. Our mind and the thoughts we tell ourselves and the resulting emotions that those thoughts create is what determines our reality.
I am here as an example as proof that we were born to be creators, not simply victims to our circumstances. I knew this terrifying experience was happening for me to teach me the lessons I needed to know in order to become my future self, the person who I am destined to be.  I will gladly help anyone who would like to know more.  Here is a snippet of my experience.

Recorded in April 2021.

node.text:
Let’s face it: If you keep the same routine as yesterday, it makes sense that your tomorrow is going to be a lot like yesterday. Your future is just a rerun of your past. That’s because your yesterday is creating your tomorrow.

We could say that your mind and body are in the known—the same predictable future based on what you did in the same familiar past—and in that known, certain future there’s no room for the unknown. In fact, if something new happened, if something unknown were to unfold in your life at that moment to change the same predictable timeline of your day, you’d probably be annoyed at the disruption of your routine. You might say, “Can you come back tomorrow? This is not the right time.”

The fact is, there’s no room for the unknown in a predictable life. But being predictable is not how the unknown works. The unknown is unfamiliar, uncertain—but it’s also exciting because it occurs in ways you cannot expect or anticipate. So let me ask you: How much room in your routine, predictable life do you have for the unknown?

I suspect that you are reading this because you know there’s more to life than what you have already experienced. Are you willing to make room for something new?

node.text:
The corresponding states of mind that correlate with stress truly are the reasons why we are controlled by our emotions, live by a lower denominator of energy, and remain trapped by a set of beliefs rooted in fear. These so-called normal psychological states have been accepted by most as ordinary and common. They are the real “altered states” of consciousness. 

Anxiety, depression, frustration, anger, guilt, pain, worry, and sadness—the emotions regularly expressed by billions of people—are why the masses live life knocked out of balance and altered from the true self. Maybe the supposed altered states of consciousness achieved in meditation during truly mystical moments are actually the “natural” human states of consciousness that we should strive to live by on a regular basis. I accept that contention as my truth. 

It's time to wake up and become the living example of the truth. When you and I “in-body” such ideals as truth and make them a habit, they innately become part of us.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr Joe Dispenza on September 14, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '"All things material come from the invisible field of the immaterial, beyond space and time." -Dr Joe Dispenza @drjoedispenza 02u0696'.

node.text:
The future reality we create in our minds does not yet provide any sensory feedback, and by the quantum model, our senses should be the last to experience what we create. For this reason, many of us make materialism our law, and we go unconscious when we don’t witness the manifestation in our 3D reality. 

I want to remind you that all things material come from the invisible field of the immaterial, beyond space and time. Simply said, by planting seeds in this world, you see that in time they bear fruit. If you can experience a dream so completely in mind and emotion within the inner world of potentials, then it has already happened. So just surrender; it has to sprout into your outer life.

But here is the hardest part of this whole process: making or taking the time for your precious self to actually do it. 

For what you create in meditation to manifest in your physical world, you must sow the seeds of intention and tend to the soil to cultivate their growth over time. Like a gardener who creates all the right conditions and then waits patiently for the seeds to sprout, you have to be patient as the process unfolds. What seeds are you planting, and what fruit do you hope those seeds will eventually bear?

node.text:
Many people who meditate reach a point where they feel overwhelmed in some way. This may appear in many forms: physical pain, emotional distress, nausea, panic, or another type of dis-ease. When people hit that wall, they wrongly assume they are doing something wrong in their meditation. In the perception of that person who is confronted by the unknown, it’s perfectly logical to draw the conclusion that they can’t control their mind. 

Yes, the mind seems out of control—but you have stepped into noticing that state and being present with it. Most people identify with their thoughts so strongly that they don’t notice that the mind is always looking for something to grab on to. Being unaware allows them to stay in the comfortable, familiar known. It also ensures that nothing will change in their life. Once you have chosen to accept that there will be discomfort and you choose to proceed anyway, you are on the path to change. 

When you notice the subconscious programs that control how you think and feel, you start reclaiming control over your life. If you feel overwhelmed in meditation, stay for as long as you can. There’s nothing wrong with getting up if you feel unable to continue—but come back to your practice tomorrow. Don’t let the discomfort of uncertainty deter you from your intention. You are training yourself to become greater than the emotions and thoughts that sabotage you. You are clearing out the subconscious programs that have been blocking the emergence of a miracle—and that miracle is who you really are.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr Joe Dispenza on September 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '"If you remain in survival mode, you never have the opportunity to believe in yourself." Dr Joe Dispenza @drjoedispenza create'.

node.text:
For years, I’ve been thinking about how we’re all constantly programmed into self-limiting beliefs; that is, believing that we need something outside of us to change how we feel inside of us. This is what advertising is all about—the never-ending dependence on, and consumption of, external sources to make us feel better. This belief, which reminds us of our separation from wholeness, is incessantly ingrained in us through the media, television shows, commercials, the news, video games, websites, and sometimes even music. 

It’s a simple strategy, really: If you can suspend people in the feelings of lack, fear, anger, opposition, prejudice, pain, sadness, and anxiety, they remain dependent on someone or something outside of them to make those feelings go away. If you remain in a perpetual state of busyness and are always preoccupied in survival emotions, you never actually have the opportunity to believe in yourself.

But what if it was possible to undo or reverse that programming so you had unlimited beliefs about yourself and your life? When you meditate, you move into alpha and theta brain-wave states. But if we can create these states with our eyes open, we expose ourselves to information relevant to our dreams, and we can reprogram ourselves into supernatural states rather than the unconscious states we experience daily. 

What empowering new thoughts and beliefs are you programming your mind with?

node.text:
Most people naturally create from a place of separation. When you see some “thing” that you want or like, and recognize that you don’t have it, you experience lack or separation. Naturally, if you want it, you start imagining having it. You automatically create a scene in your mind where you have that thing, but when you open your eyes, you remember you don’t have it and you experience even more lack. 

Then you try harder. You wish, hope, and pray. In fact, you are unconsciously waiting for the experience to happen to change in your life in order to take away the lack and separation that you feel within. Most people don’t understand that they need to change on the inside in order to produce changes in their external world. 

Remember, the heart is the center of wholeness, the union of polarity—the opposite of lack. When you create heart coherence, more energy goes to the brain and influences your imagination. Now you are restoring energy back in the heart and back in the brain. 

The Formula Online Course is a great tool to learn how to access brain and heart coherence. Click the link in bio to discover our exclusive bundles for The Formula Online Course, available only this Labor Day weekend. 

What will you do with all that available energy? Comment below.

node.text:
For true change to happen, we must become familiar with our old, programed self, and become so conscious of who we have been that we never go unconscious again. Take some time to deconstruct your present personality, which is connected to your present personal reality. What old thoughts do you need to stop thinking? Maybe these thoughts include: “I can’t, I don’t have enough time, I’ll start tomorrow, I want to give up.” 

What habits and behaviors do you want to stop demonstrating? These could be actions like complaining, blaming others, making excuses, and rushing through things. What familiar feelings do you have to stop experiencing? How do you frequently feel? What emotions do you experience on a regular basis? What are the familiar feelings that keep you from believing in your future?

The first step to change is to become conscious of who you are. We have to reflect on how we are doing each day so we can step out of the predictable future and create something new. Learn more about our exclusive bundles for The Formula Online Course, available only this Labor Day weekend. 

Click the link in bio to access.

For many years now, I’ve been passionate about the mystical. Each time I have one of these profound and super-lucid experiences, they create lasting changes within me that deepen my understanding of myself and my connection to the mystery of life. 

Once you have a mystical experience and get your first glance behind the veil, you can never go back to business as usual, and with every subsequent mystical experience you have, you move closer to source, wholeness, oneness, and the indivisible unified field. 

The good news is that mystical experiences are no longer relegated to people like Teresa of Avila, Francis of Assisi, or a Buddhist monk who’s been meditating for 40 years. Every person is capable of engaging, experiencing, and accessing the mystical. 

If you have had a mystical experience during meditation, you have glanced behind the veil of our 3D reality. What was that mystical experience like, and how did it feel?
